        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Disappointed in quantity of pork. Only 3,000 or 4,000.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Durham Hall</placeName> <date when="1815-01-06">Jany 6th 1815</date></p>
<p>Dear <persName>Son</persName></p>

<p>Not a word from <persName>Stephen </persName>and <persName>Bruley </persName>(?) as Yet. the Mail will
arrive from <placeName>Herculanm </placeName><date when="1815-01-06">this evening</date> and I hope for information</p>

<p>I have been all this week geting in my hogs and After much time
spent I shall be disappointed in the quantity expected, shall not have
over 4 thousand. If you can lett me have 3 or 4 thousand I shall be
willing to give a full price I have sent to <placeName>Herculaneum </placeName>and have a
hope I may obtain a few thousand, but have my Doubts, I can not put
my furnace on Blast untill my Pork is Killed, <persName>Captain M</persName> thinks
<persName>Stephen </persName>Has made the Purchase&#8212;If so I shall want Pork&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>M Austin</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed] : <persName>Mr. James Bryan</persName> <placeName>Hazel Cottage</placeName></p>

        </div1>
    </body>
